# release-workflow-planning-assumptions-and-risks — History

## v1.2.0 (2026-06-20)

**Changed by:** R2 re-re-plan of Odysseus GitHub issue #189 (automated release workflow for the meta-repo). The R1 plan got a NOGO on a SINGLE cross-artifact finding: the plan's CHANGELOG edit wrote the `[Unreleased]` footer as `…/commits/main`, but the SAME plan's `release.test.sh` test #3 asserted the footer matched a `compare/…HEAD` regex — the prescribed file could not pass the prescribed test. R2 resolved it with the tagless root-SHA compare form and a producer/validator cross-check discipline.
**Verification:** unverified (still planning-phase; nothing executed in CI — but the root-commit lookup `git rev-list --max-parents=0 HEAD` = `b10bfdd` was real)

### What changed
- Added the **cross-artifact self-contradiction** lesson: when a plan authors BOTH a producer (file/edit) and its validator (test/grep/regex), they must be stated in ONE canonical form and cross-checked verbatim. A plan whose producer fails its own validator is a NOGO even with zero external/factual errors (plan-vs-plan internal inconsistency, distinct from plan-vs-repo issue-vs-reality). New When-to-Use bullet, new Failed-Attempts row, new Quick Reference rows (#7), and a producer/validator cross-check checklist in Results & Parameters.
- Added the **tagless `compare/<root-sha>...HEAD`** technique: for a never-tagged repo, neither a phantom `compare/v0.1.0...HEAD` (404 — no tag) nor a bare `…/commits/main` (valid but fails a `compare/…HEAD` regex) works. Use the repo ROOT commit as the compare base — `git rev-list --max-parents=0 HEAD` (Odysseus root = `b10bfdd`). It is a valid non-404 URL for any reachable ref, needs no tag, AND fits a `compare/…HEAD` regex. New Quick Reference row (#8), Failed-Attempts row, and a dedicated Results & Parameters block.
- Made the footer regex **tolerant of both a SHA base now and a `vX.Y.Z` base later**: `compare/[0-9a-fv.]+\.\.\.HEAD`, paired with a SEPARATE negative assertion that rejects phantom v-tag links (`releases/tag/v[0-9]|compare/v[0-9]`) — designed so the root-SHA base (no `v` prefix) cannot trip the rejection.
- Reinforced in the source-trust area that the reviewer **greps generated artifacts against generated tests**, so the plan author must run the same cross-grep before submitting.
- Bumped `version` 1.1.0 → 1.2.0 (additive new findings; not a core-recommendation rewrite). Added tags: `changelog-footer`, `compare-url`, `root-commit`, `cross-artifact-consistency`, `test-artifact-parity`, `tomllib`. Updated `date` to 2026-06-20.

### Why
The R1 plan was factually clean but internally inconsistent: the file it told the implementer to write could not pass the test it told the implementer to add. A reviewer greps one against the other and the contradiction surfaces immediately. The durable lessons: (1) for every assertion in a generated test, confirm the generated artifact satisfies it verbatim — cross-grep before submitting; (2) a never-tagged repo's `[Unreleased]` footer must satisfy both "valid URL" and "matches the team-convention regex", and only the root-SHA compare form does both.

